  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Vincent's Word Studies",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Professing (ἐπαγγελλομέναις)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "In the sense of professing only in the Pastorals. In Titus 1:2, and everywhere else in N.T. it means promise. See Acts 7:5; Romans 4:21; Galatians 3:19, etc.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "In the sense of professing only in the Pastorals. In ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Titus 1:2",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", and everywhere else in N.T. it means promise. See ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Acts 7:5",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Romans 4:21",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Galatians 3:19",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", etc.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Godliness (θεοσεβείαν)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "N.T.o. Several times in lxx. The adjective θεοσεβής worshipping God, John 9:31. It is  equals  εὐσέβεια. See 1 Timothy 2:2. Const. by good works with professing godliness: omit the parenthesis which - godliness; take which (ὅ) as  equals  with that which (ἐν τούτῳ ὅ) and construe it with adorn. The whole will then read: \"That women adorn themselves in modest apparel, with shamefastness and sobriety; not with braided hair, or gold, or pearls, or costly array, but (adorn themselves) with that which becometh women professing godliness through good works.\" ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "N.T.o. Several times in lxx. The adjective θεοσεβής worshipping God, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "John 9:31",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". It is  equals  εὐσέβεια. See ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 Timothy 2:2",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". Const. by good works with professing godliness: omit the parenthesis which - godliness; take which (ὅ) as  equals  with that which (ἐν τούτῳ ὅ) and construe it with adorn. The whole will then read: \"That women adorn themselves in modest apparel, with shamefastness and sobriety; not with braided hair, or gold, or pearls, or costly array, but (adorn themselves) with that which becometh women professing godliness through good works.\" ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
